{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01N6ZANqCcyHBe3zjdrNHshV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the case. This is the `transport-additional-ca-trust` case. The precondition log shows that:\n1. `es_env_ready` probe saw 7 running pods (inherited cluster, not fresh build) - so it SKIPPED the apply phase\n2. `transport_ca_bundle_fixture` applied (the configmap was missing on the inherited cluster)\n\nSince `es_env_ready` was skipped (because pods were already running), the destructive fresh-build path didn't run. But on the fresh-build path, it would:\n1. Create secrets `es-transport-ca1` and `es-transport-ca2` \n2. Create the configmap `es-transport-ca-bundle`\n3. Create TLS certs signed by two different CAs\n4. Then the agent's task is to make nodes trust both CAs\n\nOn the inherited cluster, only the `transport_ca_bundle_fixture` ran (creating a fresh 2-cert CA bundle). The secrets `es-transport-ca1` and `es-transport-ca2` may or may not exist. The prompt says the cluster is \"degraded and running below the expected 3 nodes,\" but kubectl shows 3/3 pods running, so I need to dig deeper into what's actually degraded.\n\nLet me check what the oracle is validating.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2864,"cache_read_input_tokens":40427,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2864},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"30edf2ef-bdf1-46e1-a3d5-a7082b294e9f","uuid":"4ac407b0-8931-44bc-8b62-85e0f79311bf","request_id":"req_011CccGX2zjXvibYavNCw48R"}
